Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with coding theory and minimum distance of codes. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents list decoding algorithms for a class of codes. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial objects such as codes and point ensembles. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the efficiency of the weighted Reed-Muller code construction. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with affine variety codes, which have connections to algebraic geometry.
